#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:44
msgid "How you can help"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:45
msgid "You can help participate in the KDE Linux project in many ways:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:47
msgid "**Help KDE Linux reach a wider audience**, especially if you’re a tech journalist or other influencer. The more people know about KDE Linux, the more chance the project has of receiving the love it needs to succeed."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:48
msgid "**Daily-drive KDE Linux** or put it on a secondary machine, especially if you’re a developer or adventurous power user. [Follow the installation instructions](docs/install) to the letter; finding mistakes in the installation process and discrepancies in the documentation is also important."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:49
msgid "**Test less-common hardware**, especially [NVIDIA GPUs](https://invent.kde.org/kde-linux/kde-linux/-/issues/281) and [using the experimental delta update feature on spinning hard disks](https://invent.kde.org/kde-linux/kde-linux/-/issues/280). Other testing on less-common hardware is also appreciated."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:50
msgid "**Report bugs**: issues with KDE Linux itself (initial system setup, device compatibility, integration between components, etc.) should be reported on [invent.kde.org](https://invent.kde.org/kde-linux/kde-linux/-/issues/). Issues in KDE software — especially the experience of using it in a Flatpak — should be reported on [bugs.kde.org](https://bugs.kde.org/)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:51
msgid "**Help develop KDE Linux**, especially if you have an interest in operating systems (particularly immutable ones). There’s lots to do. [Chat with the devs](https://matrix.to/#/%23kde-linux:kde.org) and [submit merge requests](https://invent.kde.org/kde-linux/kde-linux/-/merge_requests). If you’re working on a similar OS, tell us about your experience, and we can compare notes and work on solutions together. Shared knowledge improves all projects."
msgstr ""

