msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:76
msgid "Things to be aware of"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:78
msgid "![Computer with squashed banana wallpaper](/linux/Computer-Screen-_ripe_banana.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:79
msgid "</div>\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:81
msgid "**KDE Linux is Alpha software.** Do not install it on your non-technical uncle’s computer or across the accounting department at work. There are [multiple known issues](https://community.kde.org/KDE_Linux#Current_state) (make sure nothing in there is a deal-breaker for you). KDE Linux has only received limited testing so far, and there will be regressions and bad builds you’ll have to roll back. Data loss has not been experienced yet, but anything is possible. Deploy a robust backup system. Expect some adventures."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:82
msgid "**Opportunities for customizing the base OS are extremely limited.** As an “immutable base” operating system, KDE Linux deliberately limits system-level customization to preserve reliability. Don’t go starting and stopping Systemd services except to debug or fix reported bugs. Don’t try hacks to customize your Plymouth splash screen or SDDM theme."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:83
msgid "**The experience of using an older NVIDIA GPU is rough.** [Manual setup](/docs/pre-turing-nvidia) is currently required for anything older than an NVIDIA GTX 1630 to even work at all, and they are essentially untested. Here be dragons. You’ve been warned. [Learn more about this situation here](/nvidia)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:84
msgid "**Do not report bugs for yesterday’s version.** That’s right: currently KDE Linux is being updated daily. If you think you found a bug… update the whole system first! If the bug is still there, go ahead and report it. {{< /section >}}"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:91
msgid "Key benefits"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:96
msgid "Safe"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:97
msgid "KDE Linux offers reliable system updates and lets you roll back to older versions if there are any issues."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:99
msgid "All code is open and auditable, and no data is ever sent to KDE unless you authorize it. {{< /linux/card >}}"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:103
msgid "Simple"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:104
msgid "The Plasma desktop environment is familiar and intuitive, offering panels, app launchers, icons, and menus where you expect them. {{< /linux/card >}}"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:108
msgid "Flexible"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:109
msgid "Set up the system the way *you* like with the customizability built into Plasma. Show off your style or turn it into a high-productivity workhorse! {{< /linux/card >}}"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:113
msgid "Powerful"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:114
msgid "KDE Linux offers a rich catalogue of professional-caliber software for [any purpose](https://kde.org/for/), all for free. {{< /linux/card >}}"
