#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:150
msgid "KDE Linux is a publicly-developed volunteer-run project, led by longstanding and enthusiastic members of the KDE community [visible here](https://community.kde.org/KDE_Linux#Governance_&_policies). The project receives financial support and other backing from [KDE e.V.](https://ev.kde.org), the German nonprofit organization behind [KDE](https://kde.org). {{< /section >}}"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:157
msgid "Information for techies"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:159
msgid "Is this “The KDE OS”?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:160
msgid "Yes! KDE Linux is the KDE community’s idea of a “reference implementation” OS with Plasma and KDE apps."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:162
msgid "Though it’s designed to be suitable for general uses, KDE Linux may be less optimized and optimizable for specific uses compared to other operating systems. KDE Linux is not an attempt to discourage people from using them, but rather to raise the quality level for all KDE-centric operating systems."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:165
msgid "What kind of base technology does KDE Linux use?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:166
msgid "KDE Linux is an “immutable base OS” Linux distro created using Arch Linux packages, but it should not be considered an “Arch-based distro”; Arch is simply a means to an end, and KDE Linux doesn’t even ship with the `pacman` package manager."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:168
msgid "KDE Linux leans on Systemd for a great deal of functionality. Updates are atomic and image-based, with the last 5 OS images cached on disk. Only the Wayland session is supported. Apps primarily come from Flatpak."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:170
msgid "Learn more about [KDE Linux’s architecture](https://community.kde.org/KDE_Linux/Background_information#Architecture)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:173
msgid "This is so cool; how can I get involved with development?"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/_index.md:174
msgid "Help is always appreciated! You can talk with the KDE Linux developers on [Matrix](https://matrix.to/#/#kde-linux:kde.org), and submit issues or merge requests on [invent.kde.org](https://invent.kde.org/kde-linux/kde-linux/)."
msgstr ""

