#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:11
msgid "The [Nix package manager](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nix_(package_manager)) is an advanced tool for advanced users that can be used to acquire virtually any free software package you can imagine from its [large, community-maintained repository](https://search.nixos.org/packages)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:13
msgid "It can be installed on KDE Linux for a single-user system. Nix stores software and dependencies under <tt>/nix/store</tt>, and keeps your [search path](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PATH_%28variable%29) updated automatically as tools are added or removed."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:17
msgid "The Nix package manager can be installed for the current user like so:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:19
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"sh <(curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -L https://nixos.org/nix/install) --no-daemon\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:23
msgid "Log out and back in again, then test:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:25
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"nix-shell -p mc emacs-nox  # you are now inside a shell with mc and emacs\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:29
msgid "Note that when you quit this shell, <code>mc</code> and <code>emacs</code> are no longer in your shell’s search path. See the next section to make such tools available persistently."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:31
msgid "See https://nixos.org/download/#nix-install-linux for further details."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:34
msgid "Persistent package installations"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:35
msgid "Use <code>nix-env -iA</code> or <code>nix-env --install --attr</code> to install packages to <tt>/nix/store</tt> and make them available in your user’s search path:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:37
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"$ nix-env -f '<nixpkgs>' -iA mc\n"
"⋮\n"
"building '/nix/store/1q2sh2f178jx9fl37gd9ks85ysfvpwd9-user-environment.drv'...\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:43
msgid "This creates a new “environment” which contains all the state changes necessary to make the <code>mc</code> package available, and these can be rolled forward or backward. This is the ''real'' appeal of the Nix package management system, but beyond the scope of this guide."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:45
msgid "Verify the <code>mc</code> command is now available for your user:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:47
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"$ which mc\n"
"/home/username/.nix-profile/bin/mc\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:52
msgid "Remove packages with <code>nix-env --uninstall</code> or <code>nix-env -e</code>:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:54
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"$ nix-env -e mc\n"
"uninstalling 'mc-4.8.33'\n"
"building '/nix/store/rqbghiyds6f7a49qiwi9gmq7bnkgn9qi-user-environment.drv'...\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:60
msgid "See the section about [[#garbage-collection|garbage collection]] below for how to reclaim space used by packages that you're no longer using."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:62
msgid "See https://nix.dev/manual/nix/latest/command-ref/nix-env.html for further details."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:65
msgid "Using <code>nix profile</code>"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:66
msgid "The <code>nix \\<command\\></code> interface is still technically considered [experimental](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/latest/command-ref/new-cli/nix3-profile.html) (more context on the “experimental” status of <code>nix profile</code> can be found in [this RFC](https://github.com/NixOS/rfcs/pull/136#discussion_r1123895460)), but in practice it’s widely-used, and more ergnomic. Tab-completion and the <code>--help</code> options for the various <code>nix</code> subcommands will also work out of the box on a fresh installation. Like <code>nix-env</code>, <code>nix profile</code> will install packages to <tt>/nix/store</tt> and make them available in your search path, persisting between login sessions."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:68
msgid "Here’s a trivial example using <code>nix profile</code> to install the code search tool [<code>ag</code>](https://github.com/ggreer/the_silver_searcher):"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:70
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"$ mkdir -p ~/.config/nix\n"
"$ cat >> ~/.config/nix/nix.conf &lt;&lt;EOF\n"
"experimental-features = nix-command flakes\n"
"EOF\n"
"\n"
"$ nix search nixpkgs silver searcher\n"
"⋮\n"
"* legacyPackages.x86_64-linux.silver-searcher (2.2.0)\n"
"  Code-searching tool similar to ack, but faster\n"
"\n"
"$ nix profile add nixpkgs#silver-searcher\n"
"$ which ag\n"
"/home/username/.nix-profile/bin/ag\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:86
msgid "To list installed packages or remove them:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:88
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"$ nix profile list\n"
"⋮\n"
"Name:               silver-searcher\n"
"Flake attribute:    legacyPackages.x86_64-linux.silver-searcher\n"
"Original flake URL: flake:nixpkgs\n"
"Locked flake URL:   github:NixOS/nixpkgs/f08e6b11a5ed43637a8ac444dd44118bc7d273b9?narHash=sha256-7vUo0qWCl/rip%2Bfzr6lcMlz9I0tN/8m7d5Bla/rS2kk%3D\n"
"Store paths:        /nix/store/l120si3zsshmf3jr7dkn5dvcj0n586xb-silver-searcher-2.2.0\n"
"\n"
"$ nix profile remove silver-searcher\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:100
msgid "See the section about [garbage collection](#garbage-collection) below for how to reclaim space used by packages that you're no longer using."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:102
msgid "See https://nix.dev/manual/nix/latest/command-ref/new-cli/nix3-profile.html for further details."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:105
msgid "Reinstalling Nix"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:106
msgid "If you've enabled the “experimental” <code>nix profile</code> feature, you'll need to disable that and delete the state files associated with your user's profile before reinstalling, otherwise you'll get an error message like this:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:108
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"error: profile '/home/username/.local/state/nix/profiles/profile' is incompatible with 'nix-env'; please use 'nix profile' instead\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:112
msgid "{{< section class=\"text-center warning-bubble\" >}} Warning: this will forget any previously-installed packages! {{< /section >}}"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:116
msgid "Comment out the <code>experimental-features</code> line in your Nix configuration file, and then delete the profile state directory:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:118
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"$ sed -i'' 's/^experimental-features = nix-command flakes$/#&/' ~/.config/nix/nix.conf\n"
"$ rm -rf ~/.local/state/nix/profiles/profile\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:123
msgid "Now you can repeat the [installation steps](#installation)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:126
msgid "Garbage-collecting to reclaim disk space <span id=\"garbage-collection\"></span>"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:127
msgid "Note that <code>nix-env -e</code> and <code>nix profile remove</code> both remove commands provided by a package from your user's current evironment, but the software actually remains installed in <tt>/nix/store</tt> until it is garbage collected."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:129
msgid "You can force that garbage collection, to reclaim disk space, with one of the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:131
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"nix-store --gc           # routine garbage collection\n"
"nix-collect-garbage -d   # remove \"unreachable\" packages from the store\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:137
msgid "Removing Nix"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:138
msgid "To remove the Nix package manager, run the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/nix.md:140
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"sudo systemctl disable --now nix-daemon.service nix-daemon.socket\n"
"\n"
"sudo rm -rf /nix /etc/nix /etc/profile.d/nix.sh /etc/tmpfiles.d/nix-daemon.conf /nix /root/.nix-channels /root/.nix-defexpr /root/.nix-profile /root/.cache/nix ~/.nix-channels ~/.nix-defexpr ~/.nix-profile ~/.cache/nix\n"
"\n"
"for i in $(seq 1 32); do sudo userdel nixbld$i; done\n"
"\n"
"sudo groupdel nixbld\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

