#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/ssh-keys.md:11
msgid "If your SSH keys are encrypted, you can configure the system to unlock them automatically in each new terminal window and tab you open."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/ssh-keys.md:13
msgid "To do this, add the following on its own line anywhere in your shell's configuration file (`~/.zshrc` for the default zsh shell, and `~/.bashrc` for bash):"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/ssh-keys.md:15
msgid ""
"<pre>\n"
"ssh-add\n"
"</pre>"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/ssh-keys.md:19
msgid "This works because KDE Linux automatically sets up a single-instance SSH agent and populates the required `SSH_AUTH_SOCK` environment variable for instant use."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/ssh-keys.md:21
msgid "Turning it off and setting things up manually is not recommended. If want to do it anyway, mask the relevant systemd service with `systemctl mask --now --user ssh-agent.service`, and then set things up to your taste."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/ssh-keys.md:0
msgid "Automatically unlock your SSH keys"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:11
msgid "There are two methods of keeping a KDE Linux system up to date: graphical, and using command-line tools."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:15
msgid "Updates are done through the _Discover_ software center app. Discover handles both system updates as well as updates for Flatpak-based apps and add-on content."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:17
msgid "Discover will notify you when updates are available; just click the notification to launch Discover and see what’s available. On Discover’s Updates page, click “Update All” when you’re ready to update."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:19
msgid "Updates to apps take effect the next time the updated apps are launched, while system updates take effect the next time the machine is restarted."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:23
msgid "Alternatively, you can update software using command-line tools in a terminal."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:25
msgid "Check for Flatpak updates and interactively decide to install them or not using <code>flatpak update</code>."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:27
msgid "Check for system updates using <code>updatectl check</code>, and install the latest one with <code>updatectl update</code>. Restart the system to apply the update."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:29
msgid "If greater verbosity is needed, or <code>updatectl</code> is not working, use <code>run0 /usr/lib/systemd/systemd-sysupdate update</code> instead. In these cases, record the output and enter it into a bug report at https://invent.kde.org/kde-linux/kde-linux/-/issues/new."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:32
msgid "Troubleshooting & known issues"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:33
msgid "If updates fail between 30% and 40% with “Input/output error”, wait an hour or two and try again. This is likely to be a [known issue](https://invent.kde.org/kde-linux/kde-linux/-/issues/304) related to updates being advertised as available before all update servers have fully synced."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/updates.md:0
msgid "Keep the System Up to Date"
msgstr ""

